    "Reich and Teeny [51] observed that users reported higher confidence in their own creativity when receiving affirming feedback from an AI, suggesting that affective context influences metacognitive outcomes.",
    "Bai et al. [54] and Coppolillo et al.",
    "[45] further demonstrated how moral language subtly shaped audience perceptions and engagement.",
    "Together, these studies highlight the value of LLMs for implementing controlled, replicable affective manipulations-advancing research on emotion, moral reasoning, and message effects.",
    "From Ethical Constraints to Experimental Exploration: Simulating Sensitive ContextsFinally, LLMs allow researchers to study ethically sensitive or operationally challenging scenarios by generating simulated content that avoids direct harm to participants."
